    "In order to find out which part of the stellar sources dominates the discrepancies, we divide the MRS stellar sources employed in Figures 12a and 12d by the line of log R EXT Hα = -5.80 (see the dashed lines in Figures 12c and 12f).",
    "The upper envelope of the log R EXT Hα versus log R median Hα distribution described in Section 5.1 is roughly above this line.",
    "In Figures 12b and 12e In Figure 13a, we show the scatter plot of log R EXT Hα versus log R median Hα for the subsample of stellar sources with T span > 200 days & N obs ≥ 18 (data points in black; 84 in total).",
    "The T span > 200 days screening condition ensures a long time span of observation.",
    "The N obs ≥ 18 screening condition ensures a large number of observation, and the stellar source subsample subject to this condition is less affected by the truncation effect of R EXT Hα > 3 × δR EXT Hα, as demonstrated in Figure 6b."
